---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import toolsData from '../data/tools.json';

const tools = toolsData.tools;
const otterly = tools.find(t => t.slug === 'otterly')!;
const peec = tools.find(t => t.slug === 'peec-ai')!;

const checkedOn = '2026-07-14';

// Scrunch is not in src/data/tools.json (out of scope for this task to add it).
// Everything below was fetched by us directly from scrunch.com on checkedOn; treat
// it with the same provenance discipline as the ledger, just not yet folded into it.
const scrunch = {
  name: 'Scrunch',
  url: 'https://scrunch.com/',
  entryPrice: '$250/mo (Starter, billed annually) or $300/mo month-to-month',
  affiliateFound: false,
};

const ordering = [
  { name: 'Otterly.ai', price: 29, note: '' },
  { name: 'Peec AI', price: null, note: 'third-party estimate only, about €89/mo; not published on peec.ai itself' },
  { name: 'Scrunch', price: 250, note: '' },
];

const title = 'Otterly vs Peec vs Scrunch: the three-way AI visibility shortlist compared';
const description = 'Otterly.ai, Peec AI and Scrunch compared on verified pricing, what each measures, and what each pays this site. None do today.';

const schema = [
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    itemListElement: [
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://geooptimised.com/' },
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Otterly vs Peec vs Scrunch', item: 'https://geooptimised.com/otterly-vs-peec-vs-scrunch/' },
    ],
  },
];
---
<Base title={title} description={description} schema={schema}>
  <section class="wrap pt-14 pb-8">
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="data text-[0.7rem] uppercase tracking-widest mb-6" style="color: var(--muted);">
      <a href="/">Home</a> <span aria-hidden="true">/</span> <span style="color: var(--text);">Otterly vs Peec vs Scrunch</span>
    </nav>
    <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-[2.2rem] sm:text-[2.9rem] leading-[1.08] max-w-[24ch]">
      Otterly vs Peec vs Scrunch
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-[64ch] text-[1.08rem]" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
      These are the three AI visibility trackers people shortlist against each other most, judging by what
      brings readers to this site. They sit at three different price points and, since June 2026, three
      different ownership structures: one independent budget tool, one independent mid-market tool with no
      public price list, and one now owned by a public company for about $225 million. Only one of the three
      can pay us anything, and we are not enrolled in it.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 data text-[0.75rem]" style="color: var(--muted);">
      Checked {checkedOn} &middot; <a class="link" href="/who-pays-us/">our commercial interest in every tool named on this site</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap pb-14">
    <h2 class="font-display text-[1.6rem] font-bold mb-2">Verified pricing, side by side</h2>
    <p class="max-w-[64ch] mb-6 text-[0.98rem]" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
      Ordered by verified entry price, lowest first. Peec sits second by a third-party estimate only, because
      peec.ai does not itself publish a figure; treat its position as provisional, not as a ranking of quality.
    </p>

    <div class="table-scroll border" style="border-color: var(--line-strong); background: var(--surface);">
      <table class="ledger-table !my-0">
        <caption class="sr-only">Otterly, Peec AI and Scrunch, verified pricing and payout to this site</caption>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Tool</th>
            <th scope="col">Entry price</th>
            <th scope="col">Source of price</th>
            <th scope="col">Affiliate programme</th>
            <th scope="col">Pays us</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="!font-semibold !text-[0.95rem]" style="color: var(--text);">
              <a class="link" href={otterly.url} rel="noopener nofollow">Otterly.ai</a>
            </td>
            <td class="data text-[0.82rem]">{otterly.entryPrice}</td>
            <td class="data text-[0.78rem]" style="color: var(--muted);">{otterly.pricingProvenance}, otterly.ai FAQ, re-checked {checkedOn}</td>
            <td class="data text-[0.82rem]">{otterly.affiliate.rate}, {otterly.affiliate.model}, {otterly.affiliate.cookie} grace period</td>
            <td class="data !font-semibold text-[0.85rem]" style="color: var(--g-verified);">NOTHING (not enrolled)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="!font-semibold !text-[0.95rem]" style="color: var(--text);">
              <a class="link" href={peec.url} rel="noopener nofollow">Peec AI</a>
            </td>
            <td class="data text-[0.82rem]" style="color: var(--g-unreproduced);">{peec.entryPrice}</td>
            <td class="data text-[0.78rem]" style="color: var(--muted);">{peec.pricingProvenance}; peec.ai/pricing shows tier names only, no amounts, checked {checkedOn}</td>
            <td class="data text-[0.82rem]" style="color: var(--muted);">None found; peec.ai/affiliate returns 404</td>
            <td class="data !font-semibold text-[0.85rem]" style="color: var(--g-verified);">NOTHING (no programme exists)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="!font-semibold !text-[0.95rem]" style="color: var(--text);">
              <a class="link" href={scrunch.url} rel="noopener nofollow">Scrunch</a>
            </td>
            <td class="data text-[0.82rem]">{scrunch.entryPrice}</td>
            <td class="data text-[0.78rem]" style="color: var(--muted);">we-fetched, scrunch.com/pricing, {checkedOn}</td>
            <td class="data text-[0.82rem]" style="color: var(--muted);">None found on scrunch.com</td>
            <td class="data !font-semibold text-[0.85rem]" style="color: var(--g-verified);">NOTHING (no programme exists)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-4 text-[0.85rem]" style="color: var(--muted);">
      Otterly and Peec are recorded in our permanent ledger at <a class="link" href="/who-pays-us/">who pays us</a>.
      Scrunch is not yet in that ledger; the figures here were fetched directly by us on {checkedOn} and carry
      the same sourcing discipline, they are simply not folded into the site-wide table yet.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap pb-14">
    <h2 class="font-display text-[1.6rem] font-bold mb-2">What each one actually measures</h2>
    <p class="max-w-[64ch] mb-6 text-[0.98rem]" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
      All three blend two different quantities into one dashboard. We separate them here because the industry
      rarely does (see rule 8 of our methodology): a brand mention is your name appearing in an answer's text; a
      citation is a source link the model drew on. They diverge more than marketing pages admit.
    </p>
    <div class="grid gap-5 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="border p-5" style="border-color: var(--line); background: var(--surface);">
        <h3 class="font-display text-[1.1rem] font-bold mb-3">Otterly.ai</h3>
        <p class="text-[0.9rem]" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Tracks brand mentions across ChatGPT, Perplexity and Google AI Overviews, and separately reports which
          links are referenced in the same answers. Otterly's own research (an experiment on llms.txt adoption)
          is graded UNREPRODUCED in our ledger, not because the direction is wrong but because we could not pull
          its headline sample size and date range off the page it is attributed to. See
          <a class="link" href="/evidence/#llms-txt-ignored">that entry</a>.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="border p-5" style="border-color: var(--line); background: var(--surface);">
        <h3 class="font-display text-[1.1rem] font-bold mb-3">Peec AI</h3>
        <p class="text-[0.9rem]" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Reports "visibility, position and sentiment" for mentions across ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini and Google
          AI Mode, and separately lists "key sources", the cited domains behind an answer. The mention side and
          the citation side sit in the same dashboard but are not the same number.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="border p-5" style="border-color: var(--line); background: var(--surface);">
        <h3 class="font-display text-[1.1rem] font-bold mb-3">Scrunch</h3>
        <p class="text-[0.9rem]" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Markets itself as an "AI Customer Experience Platform" rather than a pure tracker: brand-mention
          monitoring and citation analysis, plus an "Agent Experience Platform" that serves AI-optimised content
          to crawlers, and crawl observability. That third piece, feeding an optimised version of your pages to
          bots, is a different product category from the other two, priced accordingly.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="prose-wrap pb-24 copy">
    <div class="rule pt-10">
      <h2>Scrunch is no longer independent</h2>
      <p>
        Sitecore announced on 3 June 2026 that it had acquired Scrunch for approximately $225 million. Scrunch's
        marketing site has since moved from scrunchai.com, which now 301-redirects, to scrunch.com. This matters
        for a shortlist decision: you are no longer buying a standalone AI-visibility startup, you are buying a
        feature of Sitecore's digital experience platform, priced and packaged as before for now, but subject to
        Sitecore's roadmap going forward.
      </p>
      <p>
        This is not an isolated data point. Our evidence ledger already carries the Lorelight shutdown, in which
        founder Benjamin Houy closed a GEO tracking startup after seven months and concluded: "GEO makes more
        sense as a feature within existing SEO platforms, not as a standalone category." Adobe separately agreed
        to acquire Semrush for about $1.9 billion. The Scrunch acquisition is a second, larger data point in the
        same direction. Full grading: <a class="link" href="/evidence/#geo-is-a-category">the evidence ledger</a>.
      </p>
      <h2>A single blended score is measuring three different populations</h2>
      <p>
        Kevin Indig's Consensus Gap study, 3.7 million URL citations across a 20,000-prompt sample on ChatGPT,
        Perplexity and Google AI Overviews, found that only 2.37% of cited URLs appear across all three engines;
        91.07% appear in exactly one. Any tracker, including all three above, that reports one number for "AI
        visibility" is averaging near-disjoint populations. Ask which engines a plan actually covers before
        comparing headline prices. Full grading:
        <a class="link" href="/evidence/#consensus-gap">the evidence ledger</a>.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[0.9rem]">
        A wider view, including suites with AI visibility add-ons and content tools, is at
        <a class="link" href="/ai-visibility-tools-compared/">every AI visibility tool compared</a>. If Peec is
        your starting point, see <a class="link" href="/peec-ai-alternatives/">Peec AI alternatives</a> for the
        full field it competes with.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
